local printer = peripheral.wrap("bottom")
 
function msg(gap, line, text) 
    printer.setCursorPos(gap,line)
    text = printer.write(text)
end 
 
if printer.newPage() then
    for i = 1,10 do
        msg(i,i,"#")
    end
    
    printer.setPageTitle("test")
    printer.endPage()
else
    error("Page could not be created.")
end

title: Stop CPU, RAM,
content:
import os
import psutil
import sys

def check_resources(limit_cpu_percent, limit_ram_mb):
    pid = os.getpid()
    py = psutil.Process(pid)

    cpu_usage = py.cpu_percent()
    ram_usage = py.memory_info()[0] / 2. ** 20  # Convert bytes to MB

    if cpu_usage > limit_cpu_percent or ram_usage > limit_ram_mb:
        print('CPU or Memory limit exceeded...stopping')
        sys.exit()

# Use it in your code like this
while True:  # or your main loop
    # your code here
    check_resources(limit_cpu_percent=80, limit_ram_mb=500)

title: [Roblox] - Tadachii's ESP GUI
content:
local playerGui = game.Players.LocalPlayer:WaitForChild("PlayerGui")

-- check if the ScreenGui already exists, if it does, destroy it and remove BillboardGuis
if playerGui:FindFirstChild("TadachiisESP") then
    playerGui:FindFirstChild("TadachiisESP"):Destroy()

    for _, player in ipairs(game.Players:GetPlayers()) do
        local billboardGui = player.Character and player.Character:FindFirstChild("Head") and player.Character.Head:FindFirstChild("PlayerBillboardGui")
        if billboardGui then
            billboardGui:Destroy()
        end
    end
end

-- create ScreenGui
local screenGui = Instance.new("ScreenGui")
screenGui.Name = "TadachiisESP"
screenGui.Parent = playerGui
screenGui.DisplayOrder = 1

-- create Frame
local holder = Instance.new("Frame")
holder.Name = "Holder"
holder.Parent = screenGui
holder.Size = UDim2.new(0, 200, 0, 100) -- size of the frame
holder.Position = UDim2.new(0.5, -100, 0.5, -50) -- position of the frame at the center of the screen
holder.BackgroundColor3 = Color3.new(1, 1, 1) -- white background
holder.BackgroundTransparency = 0.5 -- semi-transparent
holder.Draggable = true -- makes the frame draggable
holder.Active = true

-- create TextLabel
local titleLabel = Instance.new("TextLabel")
titleLabel.Name = "TitleLabel"
titleLabel.Text = "Tadachii's ESP GUI"
titleLabel.TextScaled = true
titleLabel.Parent = holder
titleLabel.Size = UDim2.new(1, 0, 0.5, 0) -- fills half of the frame
titleLabel.BackgroundColor3 = Color3.new(1, 1, 1) -- white background
titleLabel.TextColor3 = Color3.new(0, 0, 0) -- black text
titleLabel.BackgroundTransparency = 0.5 -- semi-transparent

-- create TextLabel for Status
local statusLabel = Instance.new("TextLabel")
statusLabel.Name = "StatusLabel"
statusLabel.Text = ""
statusLabel.Parent = holder
statusLabel.Size = UDim2.new(1, 0, 0.25, 0) -- fills one-fourth of the frame below the TitleLabel
statusLabel.Position = UDim2.new(0, 0, 0.5, 0) -- aligns the text label to the bottom of the frame
statusLabel.BackgroundColor3 = Color3.new(1, 1, 1) -- white background
statusLabel.TextColor3 = Color3.new(0, 0, 0) -- black text
statusLabel.BackgroundTransparency = 0.5 -- semi-transparent
statusLabel.TextScaled = true -- enable text scaling for the status label

-- create TextButton for Status
local statusButton = Instance.new("TextButton")
statusButton.Name = "StatusButton"
statusButton.Text = "Off"
statusButton.Parent = holder
statusButton.Size = UDim2.new(1, 0, 0.25, 0) -- fills one-fourth of the frame below the StatusLabel
statusButton.Position = UDim2.new(0, 0, 0.75, 0) -- aligns the button to the bottom of the frame
statusButton.BackgroundColor3 = Color3.new(1, 1, 1) -- white background
statusButton.TextColor3 = Color3.new(0, 0, 0) -- black text
statusButton.BackgroundTransparency = 0.5 -- semi-transparent
statusButton.TextScaled = true -- enable text scaling for the button

-- Function to create BillboardGui for a player with name and distance
local function createBillboardGuiForPlayer(player, distance)
    local billboardGui = Instance.new("BillboardGui")
    billboardGui.Name = "PlayerBillboardGui"
    billboardGui.Adornee = player.Character.Head
    billboardGui.Size = UDim2.new(0, 100, 0, 50) -- fixed size for the BillboardGui
    billboardGui.StudsOffset = Vector3.new(0, 2, 0) -- adjust the vertical offset as needed
    billboardGui.AlwaysOnTop = true
    billboardGui.LightInfluence = 1
    billboardGui.ZIndexBehavior = Enum.ZIndexBehavior.Sibling
    billboardGui.Parent = player.Character.Head

    local textLabel = Instance.new("TextLabel")
    textLabel.Name = "PlayerNameLabel"
    textLabel.Text = player.Name .. "\nDistance: " .. math.floor(distance)
    textLabel.Size = UDim2.new(1, 0, 1, 0)
    textLabel.BackgroundTransparency = 1 -- transparent background
    textLabel.TextColor3 = Color3.new(1, 0, 0) -- red text for the player's name
    textLabel.TextScaled = true
    textLabel.TextStrokeColor3 = Color3.new(0, 0, 0) -- black text stroke
    textLabel.TextStrokeTransparency = 0 -- fully opaque text stroke (visible through walls)
    textLabel.Visible = statusButton.Text == "On" -- Hide the text if StatusButton is "Off"
    textLabel.Parent = billboardGui
end

-- Function to update player ESP distance
local function updatePlayerESP()
    local localCharacter = game.Players.LocalPlayer.Character
    if not localCharacter then
        return
    end

    for _, player in ipairs(game.Players:GetPlayers()) do
        if player ~= game.Players.LocalPlayer and player.Character and player.Character:FindFirstChild("Head") then
            local distance = (localCharacter.Head.Position - player.Character.Head.Position).Magnitude
            local billboardGui = player.Character.Head:FindFirstChild("PlayerBillboardGui")
            if billboardGui then
                billboardGui.PlayerNameLabel.Text = player.Name .. "\nDistance: " .. math.floor(distance)
                billboardGui.PlayerNameLabel.TextColor3 = Color3.new(1, 0, 0) -- Set the text color to red
                billboardGui.PlayerNameLabel.Visible = statusButton.Text == "On" -- Update visibility based on StatusButton
            else
                createBillboardGuiForPlayer(player, distance)
            end
        end
    end
end

-- Call updatePlayerESP() initially and then schedule it to be called every 0.01 seconds
updatePlayerESP()
game:GetService("RunService").Heartbeat:Connect(function()
    updatePlayerESP()
end)

-- Now, you can add functionality to the button, for example:
local function onButtonClicked()
    if statusButton.Text == "Off" then
        statusButton.Text = "On"
        -- Add code to enable the player ESP here
    else
        statusButton.Text = "Off"
        -- Add code to disable the player ESP here
        
        -- Remove BillboardGui for each player's head when disabling the ESP
        for _, player in ipairs(game.Players:GetPlayers()) do
            local billboardGui = player.Character and player.Character:FindFirstChild("Head") and player.Character.Head:FindFirstChild("PlayerBillboardGui")
            if billboardGui then
                billboardGui:Destroy()
            end
        end
    end
    -- Update the visibility of BillboardGui elements after clicking the button
    for _, player in ipairs(game.Players:GetPlayers()) do
        local billboardGui = player.Character and player.Character:FindFirstChild("Head") and player.Character.Head:FindFirstChild("PlayerBillboardGui")
        if billboardGui then
            billboardGui.PlayerNameLabel.Visible = statusButton.Text == "On"
        end
    end
end

statusButton.MouseButton1Click:Connect(onButtonClicked)

    decrypted_data = []
    for i in range(len(data)):
        decrypted_data.append(data[i] ^ key[i % len(key)])
    return bytes(decrypted_data)

setDefaultTab("Rook")

local mkPanelname = "monsterKill"
if not storage[mkPanelname] then storage[mkPanelname] = { min = false } end

local monsterKill = setupUI([[
Panel
  margin-top: 1
  height: 70
  Button
    id: resetList
    anchors.left: parent.left
    anchors.top: parent.top
    width: 70
    height: 18
    margin-top: 2
    margin-left: 5
    text: Reset
    color: red
    tooltip: Reset Data
  Button
    id: showList
    anchors.right: parent.right
    anchors.top: parent.top
    width: 70
    height: 18
    margin-top: 2
    margin-right: 5
    text: Schowaj
    color: red

  ScrollablePanel
    id: content
    image-border: 1
    image-border-top: 3
    anchors.top: showList.bottom
    anchors.left: parent.left
    anchors.right: parent.right
    margin-top: 5
    height: 50
    padding: 1
    vertical-scrollbar: mkScroll
    layout:
      type: verticalBox

  BotSmallScrollBar
    id: mkScroll
    anchors.top: content.top
    anchors.bottom: content.bottom
    anchors.right: content.right
    margin-top: 2
    margin-bottom: 5
    margin-right: 5
  ]], parent)
monsterKill:setId(mkPanelname)

killList = {}
local lbls = {}

local function toggleWin(load)
  if load then
    monsterKill:setHeight(20)
    monsterKill.showList:setText("Pokaz")
    monsterKill.showList:setColor("green")
  else
    monsterKill:setHeight(70)
    monsterKill.showList:setText("Schowaj")
    monsterKill.showList:setColor("red")
  end
end

function refreshMK()
  if #lbls > 0 and (#killList == #lbls) then
    local i = 1
    for k, v in pairs(killList) do
      lbls[i].name:setText(k .. ':')
      lbls[i].count:setText("x"..v)
      i = i + 1
    end
  else
    for _, child in pairs(monsterKill.content:getChildren()) do
      child:destroy()
    end
    for k, v in pairs(killList) do
      lbls[k] = g_ui.loadUIFromString([[
Panel
  height: 20
  margin-left: 2

  Label
    id: name
    text:
    anchors.top: parent.top
    anchors.left: parent.left
    margin-top: 2
    text-auto-resize: true
    font: verdana-11px-rounded

  Label
    id: count
    text:
    anchors.top: name.top
    anchors.right: parent.right
    margin-right: 30
    text-auto-resize: true
    color: orange
    font: verdana-11px-rounded

]], monsterKill.content)
      if lbls[k] then
        lbls[k].name:setText(k .. ':')
        lbls[k].count:setText("x"..v)
      end
    end
  end
end
refreshMK()
toggleWin(storage[mkPanelname].min)

monsterKill.showList.onClick = function(widget)
  storage[mkPanelname].min = (monsterKill:getHeight() == 70)
  toggleWin(storage[mkPanelname].min)
end

monsterKill.resetList.onClick = function(widget)
  killList = {}
  refreshMK()
end

function checkKill(mode, text)
  local mobName = nil
  local reg = [[(.*):]]
  for x = 1, #reg do
    _, _, mobName = string.find(text, reg)
    if mobName then
      if killList[mobName] then
        killList[mobName] = killList[mobName] + 1
      else
        killList[mobName] = 1
      end
      refreshMK()
      break
    end
  end
end

onTalk(function(name, level, mode, text, channelId, pos)
  if mode == 8 then checkKill(mode, text) end
end)
--[[
onTextMessage(function(mode, text)
  checkKill(mode, text)
end]]--

--- examples NOT NEEDED
function getKills(mobName)
  -- example: warn(getKills("Troll"))
  if killList[mobName] then
    return killList[mobName]
  end
  return nil
end

function getDumpAllKills() -- test dump
  for k, v in pairs(killList) do
    warn(v .. "x " .. k)

setDefaultTab("Rook")

local mkPanelname = "monsterKill"
if not storage[mkPanelname] then storage[mkPanelname] = { min = false } end

local monsterKill = setupUI([[
Panel
  margin-top: 1
  height: 70
  Button
    id: resetList
    anchors.left: parent.left
    anchors.top: parent.top
    width: 70
    height: 18
    margin-top: 2
    margin-left: 5
    text: Reset
    color: red
    tooltip: Reset Data
  Button
    id: showList
    anchors.right: parent.right
    anchors.top: parent.top
    width: 70
    height: 18
    margin-top: 2
    margin-right: 5
    text: Schowaj
    color: red

  ScrollablePanel
    id: content
    image-border: 1
    image-border-top: 3
    anchors.top: showList.bottom
    anchors.left: parent.left
    anchors.right: parent.right
    margin-top: 5
    height: 50
    padding: 1
    vertical-scrollbar: mkScroll
    layout:
      type: verticalBox

  BotSmallScrollBar
    id: mkScroll
    anchors.top: content.top
    anchors.bottom: content.bottom
    anchors.right: content.right
    margin-top: 2
    margin-bottom: 5
    margin-right: 5
  ]], parent)
monsterKill:setId(mkPanelname)

killList = {}
local lbls = {}

local function toggleWin(load)
  if load then
    monsterKill:setHeight(20)
    monsterKill.showList:setText("Pokaz")
    monsterKill.showList:setColor("green")
  else
    monsterKill:setHeight(70)
    monsterKill.showList:setText("Schowaj")
    monsterKill.showList:setColor("red")
  end
end

function refreshMK()
  if #lbls > 0 and (#killList == #lbls) then
    local i = 1
    for k, v in pairs(killList) do
      lbls[i].name:setText(k .. ':')
      lbls[i].count:setText("x"..v)
      i = i + 1
    end
  else
    for _, child in pairs(monsterKill.content:getChildren()) do
      child:destroy()
    end
    for k, v in pairs(killList) do
      lbls[k] = g_ui.loadUIFromString([[
Panel
  height: 20
  margin-left: 2

  Label
    id: name
    text:
    anchors.top: parent.top
    anchors.left: parent.left
    margin-top: 2
    text-auto-resize: true
    font: verdana-11px-rounded

  Label
    id: count
    text:
    anchors.top: name.top
    anchors.right: parent.right
    margin-right: 30
    text-auto-resize: true
    color: orange
    font: verdana-11px-rounded

]], monsterKill.content)
      if lbls[k] then
        lbls[k].name:setText(k .. ':')
        lbls[k].count:setText("x"..v)
      end
    end
  end
end
refreshMK()
toggleWin(storage[mkPanelname].min)

monsterKill.showList.onClick = function(widget)
  storage[mkPanelname].min = (monsterKill:getHeight() == 70)
  toggleWin(storage[mkPanelname].min)
end

monsterKill.resetList.onClick = function(widget)
  killList = {}
  refreshMK()
end

function checkKill(mode, text)
  local mobName = nil
  local reg = { "(.*) zabity."}
  for x = 1, #reg do
    _, _, mobName = string.find(text, reg[x])
    if mobName then
      if killList[mobName] then
        killList[mobName] = killList[mobName] + 1
      else
        killList[mobName] = 1
      end
      refreshMK()
      break
    end
  end
end

onTalk(function(name, level, mode, text, channelId, pos)
  if mode == 19 then checkKill(mode, text) end
end)

onTextMessage(function(mode, text)
  checkKill(mode, text)
end)

--- examples NOT NEEDED
function getKills(mobName)
  -- example: warn(getKills("Troll"))
  if killList[mobName] then
    return killList[mobName]
  end
  return nil
end

function getDumpAllKills() -- test dump
  for k, v in pairs(killList) do
    warn(v .. "x " .. k)
  end
end

UI.Separator()

--lua

-- Game Base Address:
local game = 0x00400000

-- List of Names:
listNames = {
    "Evil Centipede",
	"Another Name",
	"Another Name",
	"Another Name",
	"Another Name",
	"The Last Name"   --last name must be without ( , ) at the end
}

-- Verification Function:
function verify(name)
    for _, tarName in ipairs(listNames) do
        if name == tarName then
            return true
        end
    end
    return false
end

-- Target Name Pointer:
local nameOffsets = {0x18, 0x3DE4, 0x0, 0x0, 0xC}
local namePointer = readmem(game + 0x00EBFAF8, "d")
for i = 1, #nameOffsets
do
    namePointer =
        readmem(namePointer + nameOffsets[i], "d")
end


-- Function to Get the Target's Name:
function getName()
    local name = readmem(namePointer + 0x2064, "s", 51)

    -- If name is alphanumeric return it safely
    if string.match(name, "^[%w ']+$") then return name
    else
        return readmem(readmem(namePointer + 0x2064, "d") + 0x0, "s", 51)
    end
end


-- Sending Commands:
local targetName = getName()
if verify(targetName) then
		log("Sending tab on "..targetName)
		send("tab", 100)
end





-- DESCRIPTION:

-- Game Base Address:
-- The script defines the game's base address as 0x00400000, which is likely used to access various information and data structures in the game.

-- List of Names:
-- There is a list called "listNames" that contains several character names, such as "Evil Centipede," "Another Name," "The Last Name," etc. This list is used to check if the player's target name matches any of these names.

-- Verification Function:
-- The script contains a function called "verify" that is used to check if the target's name matches any name present in the "listNames" list. This function returns true if the target's name is in the list and false otherwise.

-- Target Name Pointer:
-- The script defines a pointer called "namePointer" that points to the target's name in the game. It uses a set of offsets called "nameOffsets" to access the address of the target's name.

-- Function to Get the Target's Name:
-- The script has a function called "getName" that is used to get the target's name. It reads the game's memory to obtain the target's name and returns the found name. It also performs a check to ensure that the name is alphanumeric.

-- Sending Commands:
-- The script gets the target's name by calling the "getName" function and then checks if this name is present in the "listNames" list using the "verify" function. If the name is in the list, it will send a message to the game, likely performing an action called "tab" with a delay of 100 milliseconds.

import sys
import turtle
import random
import math

# Create the Window

wn = turtle.Screen()
wn.title("Side-shooter By Daniel")
wn.setup(800, 600)
wn.bgcolor("black")
wn.tracer(0)

#Draw a border
border_pen = turtle.Turtle()
border_pen.speed(0)
border_pen.color("blue")
border_pen.penup()
border_pen.setposition(-400,-400)
border_pen.pendown()
border_pen.pensize(5)
for side in range(4):
    border_pen.fd(800)
    border_pen.lt(90)
border_pen.hideturtle()

# Create a pen to render objects
pen = turtle.Turtle()
pen.penup()
# pen.color("white")
# pen.shape("triangle")
# pen.goto(-350,0)
pen.speed(0)

# Register shapes
shapes = ["rocket.gif", "bullet_fire.gif", "boulder.gif"]

for shape in shapes:
    wn.register_shape(shape)

# Classes

class Sprite():
    def __init__(self, x, y, width, height, image):
        self.x = x
        self.y = y
        self.width = width
        self.height = height
        self.image = image

    def render(self, pen):
        pen.goto(self.x, self.y)
        pen.shape(self.image)
        pen.stamp()

    def is_Colision(self, other):
        # Axis Aligned Bounding Box
        x_collision = (math.fabs(self.x - other.x) * 2) < (self.width + other.width)
        y_collision = (math.fabs(self.y - other.y) * 2) < (self.height + other.height)
        return (x_collision and y_collision)

    def update(self):
        pass

class Player(Sprite):
    def __init__(self, x, y, width, height, image):
        Sprite.__init__(self, x, y, width, height, image)

        self.dx = 0
        self.dy = 0

    def up(self):
        self.dy = .5

    def down(self):
        self.dy = -.5

    def right(self):
        self.dx = .5

    def left(self):
        self.dx = -.5

    def move(self):
        self.y += self.dy
        self.x += self.dx

    def border_collision_check(self):

        if self.y > 380:
            self.y = 380

        if self.y < -380:
            self.y = -380

        if self.x > -180:
            self.x = -180

        if self.x < -390:
            self.x = -390

    def go_home(self):

        #print("Go_Home activated")
        self.dx = 1
        self.x = -390
        self.y = 0
    def update(self):
        pass

class Missile():
    def __init__(self,x, y, width, height, image):
        #Sprite.__init__(self, x, y, width, height, image)
        self.x = x
        self.y = y
        self.width = width
        self.height = height
        self.image = image
        self.dx = 2
        self.dy = 0
        self.state ="ready"
        print("This is the default of state: ", self.state)


    #This will set the bullets location on the board
    def fire(self):

        self.state = "firing"

        self.x = player.x
        self.y = player.y
        self.dx = 2

    def move_Bullet(self):
        #global state

        #This will fire the missile and change state
       # self.x = self.x + self.dx
        #print(self.state)

        #if self.state == "ready":
            #self.state = "fired"
            # self.x += self.dx


        #print(self.state)
        if self.state == "firing":
            #self.state = "fired"
            self.x += self.dx

        if self.x > 400:
            self.state = "ready"
            self.x = 10000

    def is_Colision(self, other):
        #Axis Aligned Bounding Box
        x_collision =(math.fabs(self.x - other.x)*2) < (self.width + other.width)
        y_collision =(math.fabs(self.y - other.y)*2) < (self.height + other.height)
        return (x_collision and y_collision)

    def border_collision_check(self):

        if self.x > 400:
            self.x = 1000
            bullet.move_Bullet()
    def render(self, pen):
        pen.goto(self.x, self.y)
        pen.shape(self.image)
        pen.stamp()

    def update(self):
        pass

class Enemy(Sprite):
    def __init__(self, x, y, width, height, image):
        Sprite.__init__(self,x, y, width, height, image)

        self.x = 400
        self.y = random.randint(-290, 290)
        self.dx = random.randint(2, 3)/-5

    def move(self):
        self.x += self.dx
        if self.x < -400:
            self.x = random.randint(390,390)
            self.y = random.randint(-350, 350)
            #self.dx *= random.randint(1, 3)



    def update(self):
        pass

# Create our Objects
player = Player(-350, 0, 40, 50, "rocket.gif")
bullet = Missile(player.x, player.y, 30, 20, "bullet_fire.gif")

x = random.randint(-460, 460)
y = random.randint(-990, 990)
enemy = Enemy( x,y ,40,35, "boulder.gif")


sprites = [enemy]
sprites.append(player)

#enemies = []
#for _ in range(5):
#   x = random.randint(-460, 460)
#    y = random.randint(-990, 990)
#    enemies.append(Enemy(x, y, 40,35, "boulder.gif"))

# keybindings
wn.listen()
wn.onkeypress(player.up, "Up")
wn.onkeypress(player.down, "Down")
wn.onkeypress(player.right, "Right")
wn.onkeypress(player.left, "Left")

#Bullet Fires
wn.onkeypress(bullet.fire, "space")

#bullet.bullet_location()
# Mainloop
#bullet.state = "ready"
print(bullet.state)
while True:

    wn.update()
    pen.clear()

    player.move()

    if bullet.state == "ready":
        bullet.move_Bullet()

    enemy.move()

    #Render Bullet byitself
    bullet.render(pen)
    bullet.update()

    for sprite in sprites:
        sprite.render(pen)
        sprite.update()


    bullet.border_collision_check()
    player.border_collision_check()

title: Upgrade Debian 8 to 9
content:
# Get latest Debian 8 updates
mv /etc/apt/sources.list /root/sources.list.old-jessie-backup
mv /etc/apt/sources.list.d/php.list /root/php.list.backup
echo "deb http://deb.freexian.com/extended-lts jessie main contrib non-free" > /etc/apt/sources.list
wget http://deb.freexian.com/extended-lts/archive-key.gpg -O /etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/freexian-archive-extended-lts.gpg
apt-key add /etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/freexian-archive-extended-lts.gpg

apt-get update
apt-get -y upgrade
apt-get -y dist-upgrade

# Prepare for Debian 9
mv /etc/apt/sources.list /root/sources.list.jessie-backup
echo "deb http://archive.debian.org/debian/ stretch main contrib non-free" > /etc/apt/sources.list
echo "deb http://archive.debian.org/debian/ stretch-proposed-updates main contrib non-free" >> /etc/apt/sources.list
echo "deb http://archive.debian.org/debian-security stretch/updates main contrib non-free" >> /etc/apt/sources.list
echo "deb http://deb.freexian.com/extended-lts stretch-lts main contrib non-free" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/extended-lts.list
wget https://deb.freexian.com/extended-lts/pool/main/f/freexian-archive-keyring/freexian-archive-keyring_2022.06.08_all.deb && dpkg -i freexian-archive-keyring_2022.06.08_all.deb
find /etc/apt/sources.list.d/ -type f -exec sed -i 's/jessie/stretch/g' {} \;

# Let's run upgrade to Debian 9:
apt-get update
apt-get -y upgrade

# Let's run dist-upgrade to Debian 9:
apt-get -y dist-upgrade

	if(level.id < logger.logLevel.id) then return end
	msg = string.format(level.format, os.date(logger.timeFormat), msg)
	term.blit(msg, string.rep(colors.toBlit(level.text), string.len(msg)), string.rep(colors.toBlit(level.background), string.len(msg)))
	print("")
end

local logo = [[
  _____          _                    ___  ____
 |  ___|_ _  ___| |_ ___  _ __ _   _ / _ \/ ___|
 | |_ / _` |/ __| __/ _ \| '__| | | | | | \___ \
 |  _| (_| | (__| || (_) | |  | |_| | |_| |___) |
 |_|  \__,_|\___|\__\___/|_|   \__, |\___/|____/
                               |___/    
]]
 
local time = os.time()
local formattedTime = textutils.formatTime(time, false)
local version = os.version()
local computerID = os.getComputerID()
 
local username = ""
local password = ""
 
local lastCmd = ""
local command = ""
local commands = {
    "help - Shows a list of all available commands",
    "exit - Turns off the terminal.",
    "username - Resets username.",
    "password - Resets password.",
    "power - Toggles factory power.",
    "lights - Toggles factory lights.",
    "last - Shows last command entered."
}
 
function PrintLogo(delay)
    for i = 0, 5, 1 do
        print(logo[i])
        sleep(delay)
    end
end
 
function Initialise()
    term.clear()
    term.setBackgroundColor(colors.black)
    term.setTextColor(colors.yellow)
    term.setCursorPos(1, 1)
 
    print(logo)
    term.setTextColor(colors.lightGray)
    term.setCursorPos(1, 7)
    print(" Version:", version)
    print(" Computer ID:", computerID)
end
 
function Login()
    -- Check for first time setup...
    if IsEmpty(username) or IsEmpty(password) then
        print(" Creating a new user:")
        print(" Please enter a valid username:\n ")
        repeat
            term.setTextColor(colors.white)
            io.write(" Username: ")
            username = string.lower(read())
            
            if (string.len(username) == 0) then
                term.setCursorPos(1, 12)
                term.setTextColor(colors.red)
                print(" Username not entered")
            end
        until (string.len(username) > 0)
        Write(username, 'user')
        
        term.setTextColor(colors.lightGray)
        print(" Please enter a valid password:\n ")
        repeat
            term.setTextColor(colors.white)
            io.write(" Password: ")
            password = read()
            
            if (string.len(password) == 0) then
                term.setCursorPos(1, 15)
                term.setTextColor(colors.red)
                print(" Password must be at least '3' characters long")
            end
        until (string.len(password) > 2)
        Write(password, 'pass')
        
        term.clear()
        Initialise()
        
        test = Read('user')
        print(test)
        test = Read('pass')
        print(test)
        read()
        
        term.setTextColor(colors.green)
        io.write(" User successfully created.\n")
        sleep(2)
        
    -- If user has already created account...
    else
        term.setTextColor(colors.white)
        term.setCursorPos(1, 10)
        print(" Username: ")
        term.setCursorPos(1, 11)
        print(" Password: ")
        
        repeat
            term.setCursorPos(12, 10)
            userInput = string.lower(read())
            term.setCursorPos(12, 11)
            passInput = read("*")
            
            -- If the username or password is incorrect...
            if (userInput ~= username) or (passInput ~= password) then
                term.setTextColor(colors.red)
                term.setCursorPos(3, 6)
                print(" Error: Incorrect username or password.")
                term.setCursorPos(10, 7)
 
                -- Lockout the user if too many attempts...
                if attempts >= 3 then
                    attempts = 0
                    print(" Too many attempts...")
                    print(" Please try again later.")
                    sleep(60)               
                -- Increment attempts counter...
                else
                    print(" You have " .. (3 - attempts) .. " attempts left before\n         you are locked out.")
                    attempts = attempts + 1
                end
                sleep(3)
            end
        until (userInput == username) and (passInput == password)
    end
end
 
function ProcessCommand()
    term.setTextColor(colors.green)
    io.write("\n > ")
    
    lastCmd = command
    command = string.lower(read())
    
    if (command == "help") then
        term.setTextColor(colors.lightGray)
        print(" Here is a list of all possible commands:")
        term.setTextColor(colors.yellow)
        for i = 1, #commands do
            io.write("     ")
            print(commands[i])
            sleep(0.02)
        end
    elseif (command == "exit") then
        term.clear()
        term.setCursorPos(15, 10)
        term.setTextColor(colors.yellow)
        print("Goodbye.")
        sleep(2)
        os.shutdown()
    elseif (command == username) or (command == password) then
        Login()
    elseif (command == "power") then
        bundle = rs.getBundledInput("top")
        if (rs.testBundledInput("top", colors.pink)) then
            rs.setBundledOutput("top", bundle - colors.pink)
        else
            rs.setBundledOutput("top", bundle + colors.pink)
        end
    elseif (command == "lights") then
        bundle = rs.getBundledInput("top")
        if (rs.testBundledInput("top", colors.lightGray)) then
            rs.setBundledOutput("top", bundle - colors.lightGray)
        else
            rs.setBundledOutput("top", bundle + colors.lightGray)
        end
    elseif (command == "password") then
        Print("Enter new password: ")
        password = read();
    end
end
 
function IsEmpty(s)
    return s == nil or s == ''
end
 
function Write(data, name)
    if not fs.exists('/data') then
        fs.makeDir('/data')
    end
    
    local handle = fs.open('/data/'..name, 'w')
    handle.write(data)
    handle.close()
end
 
function Read(name)
    if fs.exists('/data/'..name) then
        local handle = fs.open('/data/'..name, 'r')
        data = handle.readAll()
        handle.close()
    end
    return data
end
 
function Main()
    username = Read("user")
    password = Read("pass")
    
    Initialise()
    Login()
 
    while true do
        ProcessCommand()
    end
end
 
Main()
